node.text:
After nearly 20 years racing at the highest level of the sport, our team decided it’s time to share what we’ve learned with cyclists of all kinds. Now we want to coach you.
 
Years in the making, the Team EF Coaching method eschews dated standards for a dynamic, real-world approach to training. We have developed a dynamic power test and training plan that better prepares riders to meet their goals. We’ve learned from our coaches and our riders about the ups and downs of riding and racing a bike. With Team EF Coaching, we get to share what we’ve learned with you.
 
Head to @teamefcoaching for more.

node.text: Today, Lachlan Morton goes back in time in search of the original Tour spirit. He’ll ride every kilometer of the race — plus the distances between race starts and finishes — solo. He’ll stop at cafés for his food, and sleep under the stars. And he’ll do it all to raise money for @worldbicyclerelief, which gives bikes to students in rural areas of developing countries. Follow his adventure at the link in our bio.

One day @ramonlozano called his friend to mountain bike around his hometown of Girona, Spain. And when he showed up, Lachlan Morton was there to ride along 🤯 

"I already knew who he was," said Lozano. "Since that day, we've seen each other many weekends and sometimes during the week. I show him the hometrails and he helps me with my English and I help him with Spanish. For an amateur like me, it's incredible to share training and adventures with him."

Not a bad deal for either of these guys. Tag your training partner below and let us know what trails you've been exploring these days ⬇️

We're honored to have you on board, Tejay. And we can't wait to see you take on your new role as DS in 2022.

node.text:
This weekend, Alex Howes and Lachlan Morton are racing at the famous Leadville 100 where they’ll take on climbs in the Colorado Rockies above 3,700 metres... 

Then, Alex will wake up the next morning and take to the start of SBT GRVL — a 225-km race over unpaved roads in the forests and fields around Steamboat Spring while Morton prepares to race the Breck Epic, a high-altitude mountain bike stage race from Aug. 15-20 in Breckenridge.

Got all of that? Head to our bio now for more on their exciting weekend of racing ahead 😜 🚲 👏
